Job Description:
1. IT Support Officers

Responsibilities:
•	Analysis, design, coding, testing and implementation system;
•	Develop/update report as required by the system owner;
•	Support all users to operate system well;
•	Testing patch/program from system vendor, before deploying to production system;
•	Perform End of Day job until finished;
•	Backup database and applications system daily;
•	Perform other related tasks as required by management; 
•	Contribute to the achievement of the Bank’s objectives and goals. Testing Exercise of Disaster Recovery (IT systems);
•	Resolves all technical issues which are related to servers;
•	Backup data daily, weekly and monthly;
•	Documents all systems changed/updated;
•	Contribute to the achievement of the Bank’s objectives and goals.

2. Database Admin Officers

Responsibilities:
•	Monitor oracle database in all production and non-production databases;
•	Monitor alert log and data synchronization;
•	Perform database backup daily;
•	Troubleshoot oracle related issues;
•	Perform testing, training, documenting oracle related tasks;
•	Perform day-to-day activities of a team of Database Admin;
•	Document all systems changed/updated;
•	Perform other related tasks as required by management;
•	Undertake any other duties that may reasonably be required;
•	Contribute to the achievement of the Bank’s objectives and goals.

Job Requirement:
1. IT Support Officers

Requirements:
•	Bachelor’s Degree in Information Technology or Computer Science is required;
•	Fresh graduate or one year experience with developing application/system;
•	Has some experience of T24 Core Banking System will be an advantage;
•	Be able to write programming language like C/C++, Java, VB.net, SQL Query script, XML;
•	Be able to administer SQL Server, Oracle, and Linux/Sun Solaris OS.;
•	Good communication skill and team work;
•	Good command of spoken and written Khmer and English.

2. Database Admin Officer

Requirements:
•	Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, or related fields;
•	Fresh graduate or one year experience with Oracle Database;
•	Good understanding about Oracle Database architecture;
•	Be able to administer SQL Server, Oracle, and Linux/Sun Solaris OS;
•	Be able to write programming/scripting language such as C,C++,Java, C#, VB.net, Visual Studio 2008/2010, Crystal report, ASP.net;
•	Good English proficiency both speaking and writing;
•	Anticipate and handle critical situations;
•	Ability to thrive in change. Fast, flexible, cooperative work style;
•	Be able to work overtime or at night.

Job Description:
1. Senior Process Improvement Officer

Job Responsibilities:
•	Maintain business process on a continuous improvement;
•	Ensure that any changes made to processes are communicated and rolled out;
•	Ensure process consistency across the branch network;
•	Suggest initiatives or improvements in branches or other departments that saw standard lift;
•	Identify opportunity to specific initiatives on process improvement and productivity uplift to enhance customer experience.

2. Process Improvement Officer

Job Responsibilities:
-	Conduct branches visit looking for opportunity for improvement banking process;  
-	Review key existing business process for improvements;
-	Develop new bank forms or applications which is efficient and convenience for users; 
-	Communicate and roll out process improvement project across the branches network;
-	Work as team to achieve common goal of Process Improvement team;
-	Handle task assign by Senior Officer, Process Improvement.

Job Requirement:
1. Senior Process Improvement Officer

Job Requirements:
•	Qualification in business related field;
•	Knowledge and experience in banking operation and process in plus;
•	Ability to work in team oriented;
•	Understand on risk management;
•	Good organizational and time management skills;
•	Strong stakeholder engagement.

2. Process Improvement Officer

Job Requirements:
-	Bachelor Degree in Finance and Banking and/or related field;
-	At least 1 year experience in banking operations;
-	Good command of English language;
-	Computer literacy;
-	Good communication skills;
-	Willing to work as a team.

Job Description:
1. Senior System Security Engineer

Responsibilities:
-	Research and Implement new system security to meet the organization's current and future requirement;
-	Daily monitoring security system status;
-	Contribute an idea to improve security;
-	Develop innovative concepts, theories, tools and techniques for analysis of IT Security;
-	Publish finding through IT Security, helping ensure high standard of research security and improving uptake of security outcomes within organization;
-	Assessment tools and vulnerability remediation;
-	Build new system related to open source for NIDS/NIPS analysis.

2. Senior Server Infrastructure Officer

Responsibilities:
•	Monitor and maintain Windows, Unix or Linux Server, administration, installation, configuration, maintenance and troubleshooting;
•	Require to test and evaluate existing company technology;
•	Provide users with appropriate support and advice related to IT issues;
•	Document all systems changed/updated;
•	Assist in infrastructure setup and support;
•	Assist in execution of backup strategy, system disaster recovery, business continuity of the systems;
•	Undertake any other duties that may reasonably be required;
•	Contribute to the achievement of the Bank’s objectives and goals;
•	Require to provide written and verbal report to manager are needed;
•	Perform others duties or tasks are assigned by manager.

Job Requirement:
1. Senior System Security Engineer:

Requirements:
-	Bachelor Degree of Computer Science;
-	A minimum 3 years demonstrated experience in Microsoft, Linux, Unix, Cisco and Security;
-	Demonstrated ability to work as a part of a multi-disciplinary research team;
-	Experience with logging and monitoring security events in a large scale IT environment;
-	Experience with monitoring change and configure management tools;
-	Understandings snort, wire shark tools and its technologies;
-	Expertise in Network infrastructure (working with aspects of configuring routers and switches), hw&sw updates; network protocols; LAN/WAN based networks;
-	CompTIA Security + Certification;
-	Knowledge of Linux Security (Linux LPIC Certification is preferable);
-	Microsoft Certification (MCITP);
-	Cisco Certification (CCNA);
-	Strong commitment to team-base processes and outcomes;
-	Strong Network, Operating System and Security skills;
-	Passionate with Security knowledge;
-	Understanding of Security controls frameworks;
-	Good team work;
-	Good English.

2. Senior Server Infrastructure Officer

Requirements: 
•	Bachelor’s degree in information technology (IT) or related fields;
•	At least 2 years’ experience in related position;
•	Knowledge with windows server 2003 & 2008 and VMware;
•	Technical experience in Unix or Linux Server administration and support is a plus;
•	Technical knowledge in Network or Router setup will be an advantage but not essential;
•	Experience in Apache Tomcat or Other Web Server;
•	Experience and knowledge in backup and recovery solutions, SAN, virtualization or system;
•	Be able to work overtime or night time in case maintenance;
•	Honest, hardworking, reliable, creatively and willing to learn more with new skills;
•	Mature and initiative, able to work independently and good interpersonal skills;
•	Good English oral and written communication skills;
•	Be able to travel in place when and where the work is assigned.
